    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (81.99) and **Kyle Schwarber** (79.42) serving as our primary offensive anchors. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment against a middle-of-the-road matchup, while **Kyle Schwarber** leverages elite BvP data and a high-leverage spot in the lineup against Mahle to climb near the top of our efficiency chart. Given our emphasis on stolen base scarcity, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.77) is a must-start; he faces a favorable 5.19 xERA arm in Buehler, and the slow delivery of the opposing pitcher creates a high-probability environment for him to steal, effectively amplifying his scoring potential despite being slotted near the bottom of the order. Similarly, **Trea Turner** (76.32) remains a cornerstone, with his elite sprint speed and a 10% order bonus making him the engine of our daily output.\n\nWhile **Junior Caminero** (70.80) secures a spot due to his high base projection, the selection process for our remaining MI/UTIL slots was tight. **Hyeseong Kim** (54.17) narrowly edged out internal options due to his platoon advantage, though he remains a marginal play as we await official lineup confirmation. **Dillon Dingler** (63.89) also provides sneaky value; his score is buoyed significantly by a 19% boost against the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill profile, making him a high-efficiency start for the catcher position. Conversely, **Luke Raley** (45.65) is our most tenuous start, kept in the lineup largely because his matchup against Ryan offers a rare opportunity to exploit a slow pitcher delivery for an opportunistic swipe. \n\nRegarding the bench, **Colt Keith** and **Gary Sanchez** were the closest to making the cut, but both were excluded as they failed to crack their respective team\u2019s starting lineups. **Christian Yelich** remains locked in the IL slot, while **Zac Veen** continues his development in Albuquerque, leaving us to rely on our active roster to maintain game cap efficiency. We are monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** closely; should the lineups change, we are prepared to pivot to ensure we aren't wasting game caps on suboptimal platoon splits or reduced plate appearance totals.",
